main event: A witness in Winona, Mississippi reported seeing a bright, reddish-orange, yellowish-green light that was about the size of the evening star in 1954.
interesting points: The witness described the light as bright and moving across the sky for a duration of approximately 30 minutes., The report includes a comment that the witness felt her sighting was more profound than previous ones., The Air Force requested additional information from the witness for a scientific investigation., The witness experienced the phenomenon during the night with noticeable stars and no moonlight., Previous reports from the same location by the witness suggest a pattern of sightings.
sighted object: a reddish-orange, yellowish-green, bright white light
witness description: Female, 37 years old at the time of the sighting.
